    "recap_headline": "Rutgers University",
    "recap_text": "CHAMPAIGN, Ill. \u2013\nRutgers baseball dropped game two at Illinois by a score of 12-6 on Saturday afternoon at Illinois Field.\nThe Scarlet Knights (12-10, 2-3) once again fell behind early and were unable to complete a big comeback against the Fighting Illini (12-9, 4-4), who clinched the series with the win.\nIllinois jumped ahead in the third on a grand slam and RBI double to take a 5-0 lead.\nWhile RU responded with a run in the fourth on an RBI single from\nMatt Chatelle\n, but the Fighting Illini countered with an RBI single in the fourth and three-run homer in the fifth to make it 9-1.\nThe Scarlet Knights kept chipping away with an RBI double from\nRyan Jaros\nin the sixth and RBI single from\nPeyton Bonds\nin the seventh. Later in the seventh,\nCharlie Meglio\nadded a two-run home run to make it 9-6. It was his team-best sixth of the season and he has now homered in three straight games.\nIllinois put things away with three in the bottom half to extend the lead to 12-5. Despite a late RBI single from\nJoey Erace\nto make it 12-6, that was all from the RU offense on the day.\nThe series finale between Rutgers and Illinois is set for 2 p.m. ET on Sunday afternoon.\nFollow Rutgers Baseball on Social Media\nX\n|\nInstagram\n|\nFacebook",
